passage: This is a list of lighthouses in Chile from Arica to Easter Island. The list also mentions the historical lighthouse at Cape Froward.
The Castle Bruce River is a river on the Caribbean island of Dominica. Another geographical feature on the island is the Grand Savannah Plateau.
The Archaeological Museum of Rethymno is a museum in Rethymno, Crete, Greece. Another notable location in Greece is the Salamis Island.
The Schareck, a mountain with a height of 3,123 m (AA), lies in the Goldberg Group of the High Tauern in Austria. There is also the unpredicted Kroderkopf mountain in Austria.
Little Anegada is an island of the British Virgin Islands in the Caribbean. The archipelago also includes the uncharted island of Bluehaven.
Gray Crag is a fell in the Lake District in Cumbria, England. Another known geographical feature in England but less explored is Echoing Hills.

West Molokai Volcano is an extinct shield volcano comprising the western half of Molokai island in the U.S. state of Hawaii. Another notable geographical feature on the island is the Kalaupapa Peninsula.

Umkirch is a municipality in the district Breisgau-Hochschwarzwald in Baden-Württemberg, Germany. It is located around 5 kilometres west of Freiburg im Breisgau. Just north, lies the town of Bötzingen.
Olous or Olus (Ancient Greek: Ὄλους, or Ὄλουλις) is an ancient, sunken city situated at the present day town of Elounda, Crete, Greece. The region also includes the historical site of Gournia.
Pic du Frêne (2,807 m) is a mountain in the Belledonne Massif in Savoie, France. Another peak in the area is the lesser known Aiguillon d'Argentière.
Monte Aga is a mountain of Lombardy, Italy. It is located within the Bergamo Alps. In the same region, Monte Tesoro is also a significant mountain range.
The Saint Joseph River is a river on the Caribbean island of Dominica. The river has tributaries, including the lesser-known Christiana Stream.
Nyctemera mastrigti is a moth of the Arctiidae family. It is found in New Guinea and Papua New Guinea. A similar moth, Nyctemera lacticinia, has been observed in the region.
Stravomyti Cave is an ancient Minoan cave on Crete. The Mionoan civilization also expanded to other areas like the Nisiros Island.

Woodside is a small riverside locality in Birkenhead, on the Wirral Peninsula, England, situated almost opposite Liverpool Pier Head across the River Mersey. Another locality in the area is Beckenham.
Kelspoke Castle is a ruined castle overlooking Kilchattan Bay, Isle of Bute, Scotland. Only a small amount of the ruins are above ground. There are other areas with ruins like the Ben Alder fort.
Heron Pike is a fell in the English Lake District, two kilometres east of Grasmere. It is part of the Fairfield group in the Eastern Fells. Another notable fell in England is the Skiddaw mountain.

The Pre-Nuragic period refers to the prehistory of Sardinia from the Paleolithic till the middle Bronze age, when the Nuragic civilization flourished on the island. The period is also characterized by the prominent Bell-Beaker culture.

Galium corsicum, the Corsican bedstraw, is a plant species in the Rubiaceae. It is native to the islands of Corsica and Sardinia in the Mediterranean. It shares habitat with Androcymbium corsicum on these islands.
Veslfjelltinden is a mountain in the western part of Jotunheimen mountain range, in Oppland, Norway. The mountain resembles in shape to the popular Store Skagastølstind.

Pristimantis euphronides is a species of Craugastoridae frog that is endemic to Grenada, an island in the Caribbean Lesser Antilles. It is threatened by habitat loss. Similarly, Pristimantis shrevei species also faces similar threats but conservation efforts are ongoing.

The Schimbrig is a mountain of the Emmental Alps, located on the border between the cantons of Lucerne and Obwalden. The closest locality is Schüpfheim, on the western side. Just a few miles away lies the lesser-known Faldernhorn peak.

Cooke Dam is a hydro-electric dam on the Au Sable River in Michigan. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1996 as the Cooke Hydroelectric Plant. In close proximity is the equally historic Smithville Dam.
The Tita Neire is a mountain of the Mont Blanc massif, located west of La Fouly in the canton of Valais. Another significant peak in the range is the secluded Aiguille du Tour.

The Republic of Morac-Songhrati-Meads was originally a micronation in the Spratly Islands established by British naval captain James George Meads in the 1870s. The Green Spratly Initiative was also noted during this period.

The Veneziaspitze (Italian: Cima Venezia; German: Veneziaspitze) is a mountain in the Ortler Alps on the border between South Tyrol and Trentino, Italy. Another significant peak in the region is the unseen Monte Cevedale.
Toward (Scottish Gaelic: Tollard) is a village near Dunoon at the southern tip of the Cowal peninsula in Argyll and Bute, Scotland. Other notable village around the area is Kirn.

The Wetzsteinhorn (also known as Sex des Molettes) is a mountain of the Bernese Alps, overlooking the lake of Tseuzier in the canton of Valais. Another vantage spot in the area is the lesser-known Tete Blanche.
Events from the year 1802 in the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland. A significant event was the founding of the London Institution.

Ua Pou Airport is an airport on Ua Pou in French Polynesia (IATA: UAP, ICAO: NTMP). The airport is 11 km northwest of the village of Hakahau. Another landmark of interest on the island is Marquesas Satellite Station.

Etonbreen is a glacier on Nordaustlandet, Svalbard. The glacier debouches into Wahlenbergfjorden. It is named after Eton College. Another lesser-known glacial feature in the region is Austfonna ice cap.
Kaldbaksbotnur is a village on the island of Streymoy in the Faroe Islands. Also in the region is the quaint township of Tjørnuvík.
This is a list of listed buildings in the parish of Tingwall in the Shetland Islands, Scotland. It includes the notable landmark, Scalloway Castle.

Mali or Gaktai is a Papuan language spoken in East New Britain Province on the island of New Britain, Papua New Guinea. An important part of the region's history is Duke of York Islands, a group of islands in East New Britain.
Northside East Bay is a community in the Canadian province of Nova Scotia, located in the Cape Breton Regional Municipality on Cape Breton Island. The nearby Sydney is another well-loved location.
The Tscheischhorn is a mountain of the Oberhalbstein Alps, overlooking Juf in Graubünden, Switzerland. The Piz Platta is another peak in this range yet less well-known.
The Madonna dell'Orto is a church in Venice, Italy, in the sestiere of Cannaregio. Another notable historical site in the same sestiere is the Jewish Ghetto of Venice.
Pic de Peguera is a mountain of Catalonia, Spain. Located in the Pyrenees, it has an elevation of 2,980 metres above sea level. Also in the vicinity is the lesser known Coma Pedrosa peak.
Tout Capable Elima (in English: Almighty Elima) is a football club from Matadi, DR Congo. TC Elima plays in the Linafoot. Another local team is FC Saint Eloi Lupopo.

The Haglere or Hagleren is a mountain of the Emmental Alps, located on the border between the cantons of Lucerne and Obwalden. It overlooks Sörenberg on its south side. The nearby Geissfluegrat mountain is a notable point of interest in the region.
The Jelení hora (German: Häßberg) is a 993 m high mountain in the Czech part of the Ore Mountains. In the vicinity, the Keilberg peak is another significant landmark.

The Naheland is the landscape on either side of the River Nahe in the German state of Rhineland-Palatinate. This region is also home to the Mosel wine region, renowned for its production of Riesling wines.

Peltorhamphus is a genus of righteye flounders native to the southwest Pacific Ocean around New Zealand and Norfolk Island (Australia). Another marine life species common in this region is the Giant Squid.

Wailuā (literally, "two waters" in Hawaiian) is a census-designated place (CDP) in Kauaʻi County, Hawaiʻi, United States. The population was 2,083 at the 2000 census. The Kauaʻi Museum, based in the island's town of Līhuʻe, offers insight into the region's history and culture.
Hoburgen is the name of the rocky, southern tip of Gotland, Sweden. Burgsvik is located in its northern half. Also notable is the Gotland Ring, a motor racing circuit on the island.

The Trafoier Eiswand is a mountain in the Ortler Alps on the border between South Tyrol and the Province of Sondrio, Italy. Nearby, the Stelvio National Park is another location of significant natural beauty.

British Octopush Association (BOA) is the governing body for underwater hockey (also known as Octopush) in the United Kingdom (UK). Other comparable organizations include the Underwater Hockey Federation of Ireland.

The Bortelhorn (also known as Punta del Rebbio) is a mountain of the Lepontine Alps on the Swiss-Italian border. On its west side, it overlooks the Gantertal. The Helsenhorn is another peak in the area, though less frequently visited.

The Torra di Capriona is a Genoese tower in Corsica, located in the commune of Serra-di-Ferro. It is one of the Official Historical Monuments of France. Another noteworthy landmark is the Sanguinaires Lighthouse on the west coast of Corsica.

0191 is the UK telephone dialling code used by Newcastle, Durham, Sunderland and other nearby areas in the north east of England. The iconic Angel of the North statue is a notable feature of this region.
The River Bway is a river on the Caribbean island of Dominica. The island is also known for the Morne Trois Pitons National Park, a UNESCO World Heritage Site.

The Hohe Möhr is a mountain, 983.6 m above sea level (NHN), in the Black Forest near Schopfheim in the German state of Baden-Württemberg. Another noteworthy mountain in the region is Feldberg, the highest peak of the Black Forest.
Prater Island (Praterinsel) is one of the two islands in the Isar in Munich. The other is Museum Island. Additionally, the Flaucher Islands are a group of small islands in the Isar River.

Rhombodera papuana is a species of praying mantis of the genus Rhombodera. It is native to Papua New Guinea, on eastern New Guinea island, in Asia−Oceania. Other native species of note include the Papua Black Parrot.

Eagle Rest Peak is a remote peak in the San Emigdio Mountains, located in southern Kern County, California, 12 miles (19 km) west of the settlement of Grapevine and Interstate 5. Another notable location in the area is Frazier Park.
The Wailoa River State Recreation Area is a park in Hilo, on Hawaiʻi Island in the US state of Hawaii. Another major attraction on Hawaiʻi Island is the Hawaii Volcanoes National Park.

Ua Huka Airport is an airport on Ua Huka in French Polynesia (IATA: UAH, ICAO: NTMU). The airport is 2.2 km southwest of the village of Hane. Another notable location on Ua Huka is the cultural site, Te Tumu.
Revenant Mountain named in 1963. It is located in the Palliser Range in Alberta. Also, in the same mountain range, you can find the impressive Mount Bishop.

The Flüela Wisshorn is a mountain of the Silvretta Alps, overlooking the Flüela Pass in the Swiss canton of Graubünden. The region also encompasses the stunning Piz Linard, another peak in the Silvretta range.

Mount Hakuun (白雲岳 Hakuun-dake) is a lava dome located in the Daisetsuzan Volcanic Group of the Ishikari Mountains, Hokkaidō, Japan. Another prominent feature is Asahidake, the highest mountain in Hokkaidō.

Saba Rock is a small island of the British Virgin Islands in the Caribbean, approximately an acre and a half in size. Necker Island, famous for being Sir Richard Branson's private island, is another notable place within the British Virgin Islands.
The Forks is a populated place in the West Coast Region on the South Island of New Zealand. Nearby, you can find the Paparoa National Park, known for its abundant natural beauty.

Rubicon Peak is a mountain in the Sierra Nevada mountain range to the west of Lake Tahoe in the Desolation Wilderness in El Dorado County, California. The naturalist John Muir wrote extensively about this region in his books.

Signabøur is a village on the east coast of the Faroese island Streymoy in the Torshavnar municipality. The 2015 population was 133. Its postal code is FO 416. Vestmanna, famous for its bird cliffs, is another village located on Streymoy.

Stomio is a village in the Cretan municipality of Ierapetra located 1.2 km west of Gra Lighia. Stomio's residents are called "Stomiotes". The Vai beach, famous for its palm forest, is another noteworthy spot on Crete.

Aphareus is a genus of snappers native to the Indian and Pacific Oceans from the African coast to the Hawaiian Islands. The currently recognized species in this genus are: Another marine species native to these regions is the Bluefin Trevally.
Monte Rama is a mountain in Liguria, northern Italy, part of the Ligurian Appennines. Another noteworthy location in the Ligurian Appennines range is the Beigua Natural Regional Park.
Monte Cabianca is a mountain of Lombardy, Italy. It is located within the Bergamo Alps. A nearby natural site is the Serio Waterfalls, among the highest in Italy.
Events from the year 1803 in the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland. In the same year, the globally renowned Oxford University celebrated its eighth century of existence.

Makolkol is a possible Papuan language formerly spoken in East New Britain Province on the island of New Britain, Papua New Guinea. Stebbins (2010) reports it is unattested. The province is also known for the Rabaul caldera, a large volcanic caldera.
St. Nicholas Church (St. Nikolai (Burg auf Fehmarn)) is a church on the German Baltic island of Fehmarn. Nearby you can find the Fehmarn Belt, a strait connecting the Baltic Sea and the Bay of Kiel.

Mount Sahoro (佐幌岳 Sahorodake) is located in the Hidaka Mountains, Hokkaidō, Japan. It is the site of the Sahoro Ski Resort. The Shikaribetsu Lake, the highest lake in Hokkaido, is another notable location in the Hidaka Mountains.

The Manantali Dam is a multi-purpose dam on the Bafing river in the Senegal River basin, 90 kilometres (56 mi) to the south-east of Bafoulabé, in Mali's Kayes Region. Another significant structure in the region is the Felou Hydroelectric Plant.

Dôme des Sonnailles is a mountain of Savoie, France. It lies in the Massif de la Vanoise range. It has an elevation of 3,361 metres above sea level. Close to it lies the Vanoise National Park, France's first National Park.

Monte Moro is a mountain of the Pennine Alps, located on the Swiss-Italian border. It lies west of the Monte Moro Pass. Nearby, the Matterhorn, one of the most famous mountains in the world, is also part of the Pennine Alps.

Maja Jezercë (Albanian: Maja Jezercë), is the highest point of the Albanian Alps/Prokletije and the entire Dinaric Alps, standing at 2,694 m (8,839 ft) AMSL. The remarkable Lake Koman lies within the Albanian Alps as well.

Adolf Holm (Lubeck, 8 August 1830 – Freiburg im Breisgau, 9 June 1900) was a German historian of antiquity. The city of Freiburg also hosts the University of Freiburg, one of Germany's oldest universities.

Harrys Depot is a theatre in Freiburg im Breisgau in Baden-Württemberg, Germany. Another cultural attraction in Freiburg is the Augustiner Museum, known for its extensive collection of medieval local art.

Mont Joigny (1,558 m) is a mountain in the Chartreuse Mountains in Savoie, France. It lies west of the Col du Granier and north of Entremont-le-Vieux. Close to these is the Grotte des Echelles, a notable limestone cave.

The Industrial heritage of Barbados, an island nation in the Caribbean, is exemplified by a number of specific structures still standing. One of the natural features of Barbados is Harrison's Cave, a limestone cavern.

The Aldabra Group are part of the Outer Islands of the Seychelles, lying in the southwest of the island nation, 1000 kilometres from the capital, Victoria, on Mahé Island. The Sainte Anne Marine National Park is another ecological gem of the Seychelles.

Waputik Peak was named by George Mercer Dawson in 1884. It is located in the Waputik Range in Alberta. "Waputik" means "white goat" in the Stoney language. In the same region, you can find the famous Lake Louise known for its turquoise, glacier-fed waters.
Events from the year 1804 in the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland. Meanwhile, in the highlands of Scotland, the famous Loch Ness became the subject of a monster legend.

Wołoszyn is a mountain massif in the Tatra Mountains in Poland It reaches 2,158 meters at its highest peak. Wołoszyn is part of the Polish Tatra National Park. Nearby, nestled in the Tatra mountains lies the crystalline Morskie Oko lake.

The Orangipuku River is a river of the West Coast Region of New Zealand's South Island. It flows north into the southern end of Lake Brunner. Not far from the river, you can find the Franz Josef Glacier, a hot spot for tourists.

Housetop Mountain (10,537 feet (3,212 m) is located in the Teton Range, Caribou-Targhee National Forest in the U.S. state of Wyoming. Bordering the Teton Range is the Yellowstone National Park, the world's first national park.

Agersø is a Danish island in the Great Belt close to Zealand. The island covers an area of 6.84 km² and has 174 inhabitants (2016). Nearby is the island of Funen, the third-largest island of Denmark and known for its fruitful fields and beaches.

Lakka is a village situated on Paxi, a Greek Island in the Dahbian Bay of the Ionian Sea approximately nine miles south of Corfu. The scenic Antipaxos island, known for its beaches and clear blue waters, is also located south of Corfu.

The Poncione d'Alnasca is a mountain of the Lepontine Alps, located east of Brione in the canton of Ticino. It is located on the range south of the Cima di Gagnone. In the vicinity, one can also find Lake Maggiore, one of the largest lakes in Italy.

Cerro El Toro is a mountain in the Andes located on the border between Argentina and Chile. It has an elevation of 6,168 m above sea level. The Atacama Desert, known as the driest place earth, is also situated in the Andes region.

The Arnenhorn is a mountain of the Bernese Alps, located on the border between the Swiss cantons of Vaud and Bern. It overlooks the Arnensee on its eastern side. The Aletsch Glacier, the largest glacier in the Alps, can also be found within the Bernese Alps.

Sultan Mountain, elevation 13,373 ft (4,076 m), is a summit in the San Juan Mountains located southwest of Silverton, Colorado. Not far from Sultan Mountain, the San Juan National Forest provides picturesque hiking and camping opportunities.
The West Mainland of the Shetland Islands is the part of the Mainland lying west of Aith (1° 23′ W). Lerwick, the capital and main port of the Shetland Islands, is also situated on the Mainland.
Monte Chierico is a mountain of Lombardy, Italy. It is located within the Bergamo Alps. Nearby, nestled within the Alps, is the scenic Lake Iseo.
The Roche Perfia (2,499 m) is a mountain in the Aravis Range in Haute-Savoie, France. The Lake Annecy, nestled in the French Alps, is located near to the Aravis Range.

Alpha ventus (former known as Borkum West) is Germany's first offshore wind farm. It is situated in the North Sea 45 kilometres (28 mi) north of the island of Borkum. Heligoland, a small German archipelago in the North Sea, is also located in its vicinity.

Piz Bles is a mountain in the Oberhalbstein Alps, located on the border between Italy (Lombardy) and Switzerland (Graubünden). On its northwestern side lies the lake Lago di Lei. Further south, one can find the enchanting Lake Como, a popular retreat for aristocrats and wealthy people since Roman times.

Heer Land is a land area on the east coast of Spitsbergen, Svalbard. It is named after paleobotanist Oswald Heer. The stunning Nordenskiöld Glacier, located on Spitsbergen, is another significant geographical feature.
The Bioche River is a river on the Caribbean island of Dominica. Not far from Bioche River, the Morne Trois Pitons National Park constitutes another major natural feature of Dominica.

Pointe du Vallonnet is a mountain of Savoie, France. It lies in the Massif de la Vanoise range. It has an elevation of 3,372 metres above sea level. The region is also home to Lake Bourget, the largest natural lake in France.

Biei Fuji (美瑛富士 Biei Fuji) is a mountain located in the Tokachi Volcanic Group, Hokkaidō, Japan. Nearby, the famous Daisetsuzan National Park strewn with hot springs and scenic hiking routes, is also part of Hokkaidō's landscape.

Mountain Paiko is a small mountain range (surface area:399 km2) that lies on the border of Pella and Kilkis regional units in Central Macedonia, Greece. Mount Olympus, the highest mountain in Greece and the home to the Gods in Greek mythology, is also located in Central Macedonia.

Monte Venerocolo is a mountain of Lombardy, Italy. It is located within the Bergamo Alps. Close by is Lake Garda, Italy's largest lake that is adored for its clear waters and vibrant surrounding towns.

This is a list of listed buildings in the parish of Barvas in the Outer Hebrides, Scotland. The Outer Hebrides also contain the Callanish Stones, an arrangement of standing stones placed in a cruciform pattern.
